<br>
K I'll do my best to try and explain which are melee and which are not.  Starting with the mean iksar and going-counter clockwise...<br>
<br>
<br>
Iksar = warrior type melee (he's not actually a monk)<br>
<br>
Barbarian chick = war type melee<br>
<br>
Centaur = war type melee<br>
<br>
Dark Elf = shadow knight (~500pt harm touch)<br>
<br>
Aviak = druid<br>
<br>
High elf = paladin<br>
<br>
(2 in this room) Human = monk, Erudite = pally<br>
<br>
Vah Shir = war type melee<br>
<br>
Ogre = shadow knight (~500pt harm touch)<br>
<br>
Wood Elf = ranger<br>
<br>
Halfling =  druid, if i remember correctly<br>
<br>
Dark Elf = war type melee<br>
<br>
Dorf = cleric<br>
<br>
Drake = wizard<br>
<br>
Barbian guy = rogue<br>
<br>
Gnome = mage<br>
<br>
2 roving sentries = war type melee<br>
<br>
<br>
Some of the &quot;warrior type&quot; melees might actually be rogues...only know about the one barbarian cause the bastige backstabbed me once <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      <br>
<br>
Hope this helps.  If you get the camp to yourself, you can be picky and hold an all-melee cycle till the iksar repops. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
